<h3>Supplementary code for analyzing bursts in product interarrival times.</h3>
Last modification: 11 April 2008<br>
<br>
M Dobrzynski, Jordi Vidal Rodriguez, Jaap A. Kaandorp, and Joke G. Blom (2007) <i>Computational methods for diffusion-influenced biochemical reactions</i>, Bioinformatics <b>23</b>(15):1969-77 <a href=http://bioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org/content/23/15/1969.abstract>(link to journal site)</a><br>
Centre for Mathematics and Computer Science (CWI), Amsterdam, The Netherlands<br>
<br>
For questions and comments please email <a href="mailto:m.dobrzynski@cwi.nl">MD</a><br>
<br>
Input files for 3 case studies:
<ol>
<li>gene - simple gene expression,</li>
<li>rev - reversible reaction of two molecules, one fixed, other diffusing,</li>
<li>chey - diffusion of phosphorylated CheY through the cytoplasm in E.coli chemotaxis.</li>
</ol>

Every directory contains three sub-directories:
smoldyn - input files fo Smoldyn,
mesord - input files for MesoRD
gmp - sources and input files for GMP.

Content of the directory:
<ol>
<li>C code for Gillespie simulation of the basic burst-generating model <a href=burster.tar.gz>(tar.gz file)</a></li>
<li>C code for Gillespie simulation of motor protein progression along the polymer chain <a href=slide.tar.gz>(tar.gz file)</a></li>
<li>Matlab script to produce histograms with logarithmic binning <a href=mdloghist.m>(Matlab file)</a></li>
<li>Matlab script to generate the sequence size function <a href=mdburstsz.m>(Matlab file)</a></li>
</ol>
To unarchive files with code type: tar zxf name_of_the_file<br>
Archives do not contain directory structure.
<br>
<hr>
Created by <a href="mailto:m.dobrzynski@cwi.nl">MD</a>. 

